Subject: Re: [T2] 71 clutch and seal replace

On Fri, 22 Aug 2003, denny johnson wrote:

> In the Idiot Book, Muir talks about a gasket under the flywheel. On page
> 267: "Also note if the gasket under the flywheel is paper or metal so you
> know which kind to use when assembling", and 299: "Check the gasket w the 4
> holes in it. It's in place? OK."
> I can't locate this gasket w our usual vendors, is it generally reusable?
> Thoughts?

On a '71, the seal is an o-ring, not the 4-hole gasket.  the O-ring lives
in a groove in the flywheel that is sometimes hard to find, particularly
if the old o-ring is silver in color.

> There are two replacement discs available, one described as rigid and one
> described as spring. I'd appreciate any guidance as to which is appropriate.

The spring one is better for smooth engagement.

> I plan to take the advice of the list and thoroughly seal the tin at this
> time. I see there are two ~2" holes in the engine lid, under the license
> plate. I've never seen them mentioned here. Are they supposed to be open or
> plugged?

Never seen this.  There should be no air passages into the engine bay
except for the side vents.  Plug 'em

George Lyle
